CyCare Systems Inc., Phoenix, Ariz., announced a buy-back of 18% of its 5.8 million common shares outstanding from Hospital Corp. of America for $6 each. 

The company said that 20,000 of the shares would be acquired by its pension plan, 400,000 by the company, and the remainder by various institutional and other investors arranged by CyCare.
The company, which provides computerized information processing systems and services to healthcare concerns, said it decided to purchase the shares because it believes its stock is undervalued.
It said it would make the purchase with cash on hand and outside financing. 

In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, CyCare stock closed at $6, up 12.5 cents. 

